  "legalDisclaimerDocumentsText": "As a future shareholder of RealUnit Schweiz AG, you are required to take note of the following documents. These documents govern your rights and obligations as a token holder.\n\nPlease read and confirm the following documents from RealUnit Schweiz AG:",
  "legalDisclaimerDocumentsTitle": "Documents from RealUnit Schweiz AG",
  "legalDisclaimerNo": "Decline",
  "legalDisclaimerText": "The following information (\"Documents\") are provided by RealUnit Schweiz AG in good faith and for informational purposes only. The Documents are not intended for persons located in the United States of America, Japan, Canada, New Zealand or Australia or in any other jurisdiction where the provision of the Documents would constitute a violation of applicable law or where registration or licensing would be required (\"Restricted Jurisdictions\"). It is not intended that such persons have access to the Documents. Any person using this app represents and warrants that they are neither resident in nor physically present in the Restricted Jurisdictions.\n\nAny person using this app represents and warrants to RealUnit Schweiz AG that they are doing so for informational purposes only. The provision of press releases and other documents does not constitute an offer to sell or a solicitation of an offer to purchase the shares referred to in the Documents (\"Shares\"). Furthermore, they do not constitute a recommendation or investment advice by RealUnit Schweiz AG or any other party to buy or sell the Shares.\n\nIn particular, the Documents do not constitute an offer to sell or a solicitation of an offer to purchase the Shares by RealUnit Schweiz AG in any Restricted Jurisdiction or in any other jurisdiction where offers or sales would be unlawful prior to registration or qualification under the securities laws of such jurisdiction. In particular, the Shares have not been and will not be registered under the United States Securities Act of 1933 (as amended).\n\nThe Documents are intended only for permanent residents of Switzerland, Germany and Liechtenstein. The Documents may not be used or distributed in jurisdictions other than Germany or Liechtenstein.\n\nYou should cancel this process if you are not permitted to access the Documents or if you are unsure whether you are entitled to do so.\n\nBy agreeing to these legal notices and tapping the \"Agree\" button, I confirm that I am a permanent resident of Switzerland, Germany or Liechtenstein and that I am neither resident in nor physically present in the Restricted Jurisdictions.",
  "legalDisclaimerText2": "RealUnit Schweiz AG is obligated under Swiss law to obtain and retain certain information about its shareholders. As a shareholder, you are legally and contractually (registration agreement) obligated to provide this information truthfully and completely and to report any changes to the company within 30 days.\n\nPlease carefully read the registration agreement before acquiring RealUnit stock tokens via the Brokerbot. It contains details of your rights and obligations as a token holder. By acquiring, selling, holding and/or transferring stock tokens of the company to a third party, you fully accept the terms of the registration agreement.\n\nBy connecting your wallet and registering your data with the company, you confirm:\n\n• that you are acquiring or selling the company's shares on your own account and that only you control the specified wallet;\n• that the specified countries are your only tax domiciles and that you will report any changes to the company within 30 days.\n\nBy connecting your wallet and registering your data with the company, you further acknowledge and agree:\n\n• that the company is obligated under Swiss law to obtain, retain and, where applicable, transmit certain information about its shareholders to foreign tax authorities;\n• that pursuant to Article 35 of the Federal Act on the International Automatic Exchange of Information in Tax Matters (AEOIA), the wilful provision of false information in a self-certification, the failure to inform the company of a change in circumstances, or the provision of false information in connection with a change in circumstances may be punishable by a fine.\n\nThe company reserves the right not to register or to remove from the share register shareholders who violate these provisions. In such a case, you will not receive or will lose your shareholder rights. The company further reserves the right not to register or to remove acquirers from the share register based on their domicile.",
  "legalDisclaimerTitle": "Important legal notices for investors & confirmation of residence",
